<recipe>
<title>
Barbecue Bacon Cheeseburger Chili
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
COOK TIME: 1 hour 25 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 1 hour 35 minutes
COURSE: Main Course
CUISINE: American
SERVINGS: 10
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="2.0">Beef</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0">Onion</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0 oz ">Bean</ingredient><ingredient amount="3.0 oz ">Tomato</ingredient><ingredient amount="16.0 Bar">Barbecue Sauce</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 tsp ">Chili Powder</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
In a large pot or Dutch oven, brown the ground meat. Drain, and set aside.
Cook the bacon. Set bacon aside, and drain all but about 1 tablespoon of the grease.
Cook onion in bacon grease until soft, about 3-5 minutes.
Return the browned ground beef to the pot.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Stir to combine.
Crumble bacon over the chili, and stir in.
Cover, and simmer over medium-low heat, stirring as needed, for about 1-2 hours.
Serve sprinkled with shredded cheese.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>